## 9. Practical ImageJ Analysis Workflows for Neuropathology

### 9.1 Plaque Burden Quantification
```
1. Open Abeta-stained section image
2. Separate DAB channel: run("Colour Deconvolution", "vectors=[H DAB]");
3. Threshold DAB channel: setAutoThreshold("Triangle");
4. Create binary mask: run("Convert to Mask");
5. Clean up: run("Open"); run("Close-");  // morphological operations
6. Measure: run("Analyze Particles...", "size=50-Infinity summarize");
7. Report: % Area, plaque count, mean plaque size per ROI
```

### 9.2 Microglial Morphology Analysis
```
1. Open Iba1-stained section (fluorescence or DAB)
2. For DAB: Colour deconvolution → DAB channel
3. Threshold individual microglia: Manual or automated
4. Per cell:
   a. Cell area: run("Analyze Particles...", "");
   b. Skeleton: run("Skeletonize"); run("Analyze Skeleton (2D/3D)");
   c. Sholl: Draw line from soma → run("Sholl Analysis...");
   d. Fractal: run("FracLac");  // requires FracLac plugin
5. Report: soma area, total process length, branch count, Sholl intersections
```

### 9.3 Tangle Counting (AT8)
```
1. Open AT8-stained section
2. Colour deconvolution for DAB
3. Threshold: setAutoThreshold("Otsu");
4. Size filter: run("Analyze Particles...", "size=100-5000 circularity=0.3-1.0");
   // Tangles are larger than neuropil threads
5. Manual verification recommended (tangles vs dystrophic neurites)
6. Report: count per region, per mm2 (with reference area)
```

### 9.4 Synapse Density (Puncta Colocalization)
```
1. Open multi-channel image (e.g., synaptophysin + PSD-95)
2. Split channels: run("Split Channels");
3. For each channel:
   a. Background subtraction: run("Subtract Background...", "rolling=10");
   b. Threshold: setAutoThreshold("MaxEntropy");
   c. Create mask: run("Convert to Mask");
4. Colocalization: imageCalculator("AND create", "pre_mask", "post_mask");
5. Count: run("Analyze Particles...", "size=0.05-2.0 summarize");
6. Normalize: per unit area or per dendrite length (MAP2 channel)
```

